-- U.S. Retail June Comp Sales Rose 3 Percent, ICSC Says
-- Heather Burke
-- 2010-07-08T13:47:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/u-s-retail-june-comp-sales-rose-3-percent-icsc-says.html

          
          
             U.S. retailers’ June same-store sales
rose 3 percent from a year earlier, according to the
International Council of Shopping Centers. The group said
yesterday it forecast sales to rise 3 percent to 4 percent
“with bias towards a stronger performance for the month.”  
          
          


  


        